AMENDMENT XII


Section 15 of Article VIII, Lands, as amended by Amendment I approved 
December 1, 1942, and Amendment II approved October 31, 1944, to the 
Bad River Constitution shall be deleted.

Section 15. The trapping, shooting, and killing of muskrats in any 
manner within the boundaries of the Bad River Reservation shall not 
be permitted until after November 1, 1944. Thereafter such animals 
may be taken only by the Business Muskrat Fur Farm, which shall be 
operated as a permanent tribal enterprise for the sole benefit of 
the members of the Bad River Band of Chippewa Indians.
 
 

